This paper discusses transfer learning in the context of speech and language processing, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning models, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the transfer of models between different data types and distributions, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper mentions the use of Bayesian models, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
